label: NETWORK
comment: Network domain model designed to support physical and virtual networks and applications running on them. This version includes physical spaces, users, devices, networks, processes, data and data fields (separate elements in a data schema). It generates logical assets representing serialized data assets (as copies of data having a specific type within the system), network interfaces, routing tables and network paths, relationships between clients and services, contextualisation relationships between hosts and physical spaces, and processes running on a host in a physical space. and physical spaces. Threat models represent physical intrusion and attacks on devices, unauthorized access to devices and networks, unauthorized use of services, unauthorized access to data, phishing and other deception attacks (if carried out via digital means), etc. There are also compliance threat models of the main security-related data protection requirements as imposed by the GDPR (Articles 6, 8 and 9).
